h2.rule-above Body Text & Rhythm

p
  | Good typography is measured not by how much it stands out, but by how seamlessly it serves its purpose. The baseline grid provides the invisible scaffolding upon which all typographic decisions rest. When text aligns to a consistent vertical rhythm, the page achieves a harmony that readers feel even if they cannot articulate it.

p
  | As Massimo Vignelli wrote in his Canon: "The grid is an integral part of book design. It's not something that you see, it's something that you feel." This principle extends beyond print to every medium where text must communicate with clarity and grace.

blockquote
  p Typography is what language looks like.
  p — Ellen Lupton

