h3 Code

pre
  code
    | function alignToBaseline(element) {
    |   const baseline = 24;
    |   const height = element.offsetHeight;
    |   const lines = Math.ceil(height / baseline);
    |   return lines * baseline;
    | }

hr

h2.rule-above The Formula

p
  | The core calculation that makes this work:

pre
  code
    | padding-top: calc((line-height - 1cap) / 2);
    | margin-bottom: calc(desired-margin - padding-top);

p
  | The
  code> 1cap
  |  unit gives us the cap-height of the current font. Subtracting it from line-height and dividing by 2 tells us how much "half-leading" exists above the text. Adding this as padding pushes the text down so its baseline lands on the grid line.
